<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33BE3FD09FD6051B3" bold="true" box="[491,670,725,758]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Ceratoppia</emphasis>
Berlese
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C339E7D6FFDDFFB33BE3FCD3FA2E5719" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3FCD3FD93577F" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33BE3FCD3FD9A5063" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1908" box="[491,612,783,806]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33BE3FCD3FD9A5063" box="[491,612,783,806]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Ceratoppia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most common and species-rich genus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E51FCD3FB225062" box="[1113,1244,783,807]" class="Arachnida" family="Peloppiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Peloppiidae</taxonomicName>
and is restricted to the northern hemisphere. Several species are Holarctic (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2C9ACFFDDFFB33E12FCEDFB5C500C" author="Schatz H." box="[1050,1186,817,841]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="209 - 288" refId="ref4624" refString="Schatz H. 2006. Catalogue of known oribatid mite species (Acari Oribatida) from the Central American landbridge (First part). Tropical Zoology, 19: 209 - 288." type="journal article" year="2006">Schatz 2006</bibRefCitation>
) and a total of nine (plus two subspecies) are known from North America (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2C9ACFFDDFFB339F4FC8FFB7E502E" author="Lindo Z." box="[1020,1152,851,875]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref4247" refString="Lindo Z. 2011. Five new species of Ceratoppia (Acari: Oribatida: Peloppiidae) from western North America. Zootaxa, 3036: 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="2011">Lindo 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The main character states defining 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33843FCABFD3A50CB" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1908" box="[587,708,887,910]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33843FCABFD3A50CB" box="[587,708,887,910]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Ceratoppia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among the 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33935FCAAFC3E50CB" box="[829,960,886,910]" class="Arachnida" family="Peloppiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Peloppiidae</taxonomicName>
are chelate-dentate chelicerae, a conspicuous and straight sejugal apodeme, tridactyl pretarsus, and long lamellar cusps and bothridial setae. The main character states differentiating North American species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E97FC67FAE65097" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1908" box="[1183,1304,955,978]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E97FC67FAE65097" box="[1183,1304,955,978]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Ceratoppia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the number of hypostomal setae on the subcapitular mentum, and the number and expression of posterior notogastral setae; other diagnostic characters include the length of the lamellae and shape of the rostrum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB3381BFB98FA2E5719" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" box="[531,1488,1092,1116]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
Of the North American species, the Holarctic 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E08FB99FB265719" authority="(Hermann)" baseAuthorityName="Hermann" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1024,1240,1092,1116]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipilis">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E08FB99FB975719" box="[1024,1129,1092,1116]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. bipilis</emphasis>
(Hermann)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33F11FB99FA2E5719" baseAuthorityName="Aoki" baseAuthorityYear="1969" box="[1305,1488,1092,1116]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridentata">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33F11FB99FA2E5719" box="[1305,1488,1092,1116]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C339E7D6FFDDFFB23BE3FBBBFAF85289" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3FBBBFA36573A" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" box="[491,1480,1127,1151]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">(Haller) are best known. Both species are additionally represented by subspecies within their</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3FB55FA4857E4" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" box="[491,1462,1161,1186]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
North American range: 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB338FDFB56FBF357E4" authority="(Banks)" baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[757,1037,1161,1185]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bipilis" subSpecies="spinipes">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB338FDFB56FC3F57E4" box="[757,961,1161,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. bipilis spinipes</emphasis>
(Banks)
</taxonomicName>
(also 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E54FB56FA6C57E4" authority="(Jacot)" baseAuthorityName="Jacot" box="[1116,1426,1161,1185]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bipilis" subSpecies="brevicuspis">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E54FB56FAB757E4" box="[1116,1353,1161,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. bipilis brevicuspis</emphasis>
(Jacot)
</taxonomicName>
—
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3FB70FA345786" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" box="[491,1482,1196,1220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
later synonymised with 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB338E5FB70FCA95781" baseAuthorityName="Hermann" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[749,855,1196,1220]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipilis">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB338E5FB70FCA95781" box="[749,855,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. bipilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2C9ACFFDDFFB33972FB70FC095781" author="Jacot A. P." box="[890,1015,1196,1220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="546 - 553" refId="ref4110" refString="Jacot A. P. 1936. New mossmites, chiefly Midwestern. American Midland Naturalist, 17: 546 - 553. doi: 10.2307 / 2419978" type="journal article" year="1936">Jacot (1936)</bibRefCitation>
— and 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E5FFB70FA395786" authority="Hammer" authorityName="Hammer" box="[1111,1479,1196,1220]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="quadridentata" subSpecies="arctica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E5FFB70FA9E5781" box="[1111,1376,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata arctica</emphasis>
Hammer
</taxonomicName>
,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3FB12FA2E564D" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
respectively (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2C9ACFFDDFFB33871FB12FCA357A3" author="Marshall V. G. &amp; Reeves R. M. &amp; Norton R. A." box="[633,861,1230,1254]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 418" refId="ref4412" refString="Marshall V. G., Reeves R. M., Norton R. A. 1987. Catalogue of the Oribatida (Acari) of continental United States and Canada. Memiors of the Entomological Society of Canada, 139: 1 - 418." type="journal article" year="1987">
Marshall 
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB338EDFB13FCE357A3" box="[741,797,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">et al.</emphasis>
1987
</bibRefCitation>
). In North America 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E44FB13FAA957A3" box="[1100,1367,1230,1254]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="quadridentata" subSpecies="arctica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E44FB13FAA957A3" box="[1100,1367,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata arctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more commonly reported than the nominate 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33983FB2DFBBF564D" baseAuthorityName="Aoki" baseAuthorityYear="1969" box="[907,1089,1264,1288]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridentata">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33983FB2DFBBF564D" box="[907,1089,1264,1288]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is recorded only from 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB33F83FB2CFA2E564D" box="[1419,1488,1264,1288]" country="United States of America" name="Alaska" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Alaska</collectingRegion>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3FACFFA2056F1" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2C9ACFFDDFFB33BF9FACFFD73566E" author="Bohnsack K. K." box="[497,653,1299,1323]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" refId="ref3702" refString="Bohnsack K. K. 1973. Distribution of oribatids near Barrow, Alaska. In: Daniel M., Rosicky B. (eds). Proceedings 3 rd International Congress of Acarology; Prague. p. 71 - 74. doi: 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 010 - 2709 - 0 _ 11" type="book" year="1973">Bohnsack 1973</bibRefCitation>
); the latter record is likely 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB339C8FACFFB36566E" box="[960,1224,1299,1323]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="quadridentata" subSpecies="arctica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB339C8FACFFB36566E" box="[960,1224,1299,1323]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata arctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as there is considerable variation reported within 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33909FAEAFBC05608" authority="(Aoki 1969)" baseAuthorityName="Aoki" baseAuthorityYear="1969" box="[769,1086,1333,1357]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridentata">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33909FAEAFC445608" box="[769,954,1333,1357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2C9ACFFDDFFB339C1FAE9FBC95608" author="Aoki J." box="[969,1079,1333,1357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="117 - 141" refId="ref3365" refString="Aoki J. 1969. Taxonomic investigations on free-living mites in the subalpine forest on Shiga Heights IBP Area. III. Cryptostigmata. Bulletin of the Natural Science Museum of Tokyo, 12: 117 - 141." type="journal article" year="1969">Aoki 1969</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E80FAEAFA6A5608" box="[1160,1428,1333,1357]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="quadridentata" subSpecies="arctica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E80FAEAFA6A5608" box="[1160,1428,1333,1357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata arctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is common in 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB33856FA84FD5D5635" box="[606,675,1368,1392]" country="United States of America" name="Alaska" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Alaska</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2C9ACFFDDFFB338A7FA84FCB95635" author="Hammer M." box="[687,839,1368,1392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref4093" refString="Hammer M. 1955. Alaskan oribatids. Acta Arctica, 7: 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="1955">Hammer 1955</bibRefCitation>
). Both 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB339ACFA84FBF65635" baseAuthorityName="Hermann" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[932,1032,1368,1392]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipilis">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB339ACFA84FBF65635" box="[932,1032,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. bipilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E3CFA84FAC85635" box="[1076,1334,1368,1392]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="quadridentata" subSpecies="arctica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E3CFA84FAC85635" box="[1076,1334,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata arctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are widespread in arctic, subarctic, boreal and temperate areas, and overlap in the western subarctic and arctic areas (
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB33827FA40FD8756F1" box="[559,633,1436,1460]" country="United States of America" name="Alaska" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Alaska</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB3388CFA40FD3A56F1" box="[644,708,1436,1460]" country="Canada" name="Yukon" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Yukon</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB338C5FA40FC4D56F1" box="[717,947,1436,1460]" country="Canada" name="Northwest Territories" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Northwest Territories</collectingRegion>
, and Nunuvut) with 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E92FA41FA7B56F1" authority="Willmann" authorityName="Willmann" authorityYear="1938" box="[1178,1413,1436,1460]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexpilosa">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E92FA41FAE256F1" box="[1178,1308,1436,1460]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. sexpilosa</emphasis>
Willmann
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33FCDFA41FA2056F1" box="[1477,1502,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3FA63FA4356BC" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33BE3FA63FD3B5692" authority="(L. Koch)" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[491,709,1471,1495]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaerica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33BE3FA63FDAA5692" box="[491,596,1471,1495]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">sphaerica</emphasis>
(L. Koch)
</taxonomicName>
. The subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB3397EFA1CFBC65692" baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[886,1080,1471,1495]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bipilis" subSpecies="spinipes">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB3397EFA1CFBC65692" box="[886,1080,1471,1495]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. bipilis spinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from eastern North America including 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB3385BFA3DFD5D56BC" box="[595,675,1505,1529]" country="Canada" name="Ontario" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Ontario</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB338A4FA3DFCD956BC" box="[684,807,1505,1529]" country="United States of America" name="Connecticut" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Connecticut</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB33939FA3DFC8D56BC" box="[817,883,1505,1529]" country="United States of America" name="Maine" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Maine</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB33975FA3DFC1956BC" box="[893,999,1505,1529]" country="United States of America" name="Maryland" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Maryland</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB339F9FA3EFB5E56BC" box="[1009,1184,1505,1529]" country="United States of America" name="New Hampshire" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">New Hampshire</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB33EA2FA3DFB0256BC" box="[1194,1276,1505,1529]" country="United States of America" name="Virginia" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Virginia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB33F38FA3EFA4356BC" box="[1328,1469,1505,1529]" country="United States of America" name="West Virginia" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">West Virginia</collectingRegion>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3F9D8FA2C5525" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2C9ACFFDDFFB33BFAF9D8FD395559" author="Marshall V. G. &amp; Reeves R. M. &amp; Norton R. A." box="[498,711,1540,1564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 418" refId="ref4412" refString="Marshall V. G., Reeves R. M., Norton R. A. 1987. Catalogue of the Oribatida (Acari) of continental United States and Canada. Memiors of the Entomological Society of Canada, 139: 1 - 418." type="journal article" year="1987">
Marshall 
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33851F9D9FD715559" box="[601,655,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">et al.</emphasis>
1987
</bibRefCitation>
). The validity of both subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E31F9D8FABE5559" box="[1081,1344,1540,1564]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="quadridentata" subSpecies="arctica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E31F9D8FABE5559" box="[1081,1344,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata arctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33F7CF9D8FDBC557B" baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bipilis" subSpecies="spinipes">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33F7CF9D8FDBC557B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. bipilis spinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
requires confirmation as both 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33984F9FBFC0B557B" baseAuthorityName="Hermann" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[908,1013,1574,1598]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipilis">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33984F9FBFC0B557B" box="[908,1013,1574,1598]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. bipilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E2BF9FBFAD4557B" box="[1059,1322,1574,1598]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="quadridentata" subSpecies="arctica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E2BF9FBFAD4557B" box="[1059,1322,1574,1598]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. quadridentata arctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
display a wide variety of body size across their North American distributional range. Observed specimens of
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3F9B0FB4D55C6" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" box="[491,1203,1643,1667]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33BE3F9B0FD4F55C6" baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[491,689,1643,1667]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bipilis" subSpecies="spinipes">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33BE3F9B0FD4F55C6" box="[491,689,1643,1667]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. bipilis spinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also display considerable variation in body size.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB3381BF951FA4F55E0" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" box="[531,1457,1677,1701]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2C9ACFFDDFFB3381BF951FD5A55E0" author="Lindo Z." box="[531,676,1677,1701]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref4247" refString="Lindo Z. 2011. Five new species of Ceratoppia (Acari: Oribatida: Peloppiidae) from western North America. Zootaxa, 3036: 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="2011">Lindo (2011)</bibRefCitation>
recently described five new species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E5DF952FB3055E0" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1908" box="[1109,1230,1678,1701]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E5DF952FB3055E0" box="[1109,1230,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Ceratoppia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Pacific coastal
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3F96CFA4155AF" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
North America with overlapping distributions but differing in habitat preference. Three of these species were described primarily or solely from arboreal habitats 
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33EF4F90FFAEF55AF" box="[1276,1297,1747,1770]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C</emphasis>
(. 
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33F15F90EFA6855AF" box="[1309,1430,1746,1770]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">longicuspis</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33FAEF90FFA4155AF" box="[1446,1471,1747,1770]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3F929FA225448" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" box="[491,1500,1781,1805]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33BE3F929FDA05448" box="[491,606,1781,1805]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tofinoensis">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33BE3F929FDA05448" box="[491,606,1781,1805]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">tofinoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33864F929FD135448" box="[620,749,1781,1805]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valerieae">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33864F929FD135448" box="[620,749,1781,1805]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. valerieae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), one species was collected solely from bark habitats (
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33F38F929FA335448" box="[1328,1485,1781,1805]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offarostrata">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33F38F929FA335448" box="[1328,1485,1781,1805]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. offarostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
),
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3F8CBFA40546A" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" box="[491,1470,1815,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
and one species collected solely from forest floor soils (
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33E47F8C4FB2A546A" box="[1103,1236,1815,1839]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indentata">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33E47F8C4FB2A546A" box="[1103,1236,1815,1839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. indentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Distributions of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33FADF8C4FA40546A" box="[1445,1470,1816,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33FADF8C4FA40546A" box="[1445,1470,1816,1839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3F8E5FA4F5431" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33BE3F8E5FDB15414" box="[491,591,1849,1873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">indentata</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33857F8E6FD065414" box="[607,760,1849,1873]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicupsis">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33857F8E6FD065414" box="[607,760,1849,1873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. longicupsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB3393DF8E6FC475414" box="[821,953,1849,1873]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valerieae">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB3393DF8E6FC475414" box="[821,953,1849,1873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. valerieae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
span the North American Pacific coastline from north-central 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB3387CF880FCCF5431" box="[628,817,1884,1908]" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">British Columbia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F334F4CDFFDDFFB33936F880FC6C5431" box="[830,914,1884,1908]" name="Canada" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Canada</collectingCountry>
, to north-central California State. It was noted that
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3F8A3FA4954D3" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" box="[491,1463,1918,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33BE3F8A3FD9154D3" box="[491,623,1918,1942]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indentata">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33BE3F8A3FD9154D3" box="[491,623,1918,1942]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">C. indentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has increasing morphological variation in the southern extent of its distribution.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB33BE3F87DFA34549E" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB33BE3F87DFD3254FC" box="[491,716,1953,1977]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valerieae">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB33BE3F87DFD3254FC" box="[491,716,1953,1977]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Ceratoppia valerieae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the most expansive distribution longitudinally, being found in arboreal habitats near the coast and dry ground habitats in interior 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB33E4AF81FFB0C549E" box="[1090,1266,1987,2011]" country="United States of America" name="Washington" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Washington State</collectingRegion>
and southern 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDDFFB33F8AF81FFA34549E" box="[1410,1482,1987,2011]" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">British</collectingRegion>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDDFFB23BE3F839FA4453B8" blockId="2.[491,1512,783,2045]" lastBlockId="3.[491,1495,229,461]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
Columbia. 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDDFFB3386FF83AFCA554B8" box="[615,859,2021,2045]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tofinoensis">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDDFFB3386FF83AFCA554B8" box="[615,859,2021,2045]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Ceratoppia tofinoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less commonly sampled and appears to be restricted to coastal 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDCFFB23835FF39FD7653B8" box="[573,648,229,253]" country="United States of America" name="Oregon" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">Oregon</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDCFFB238C8FF39FCC753B8" box="[704,825,229,253]" country="United States of America" name="Washington" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">Washington</collectingRegion>
, and the west coast of Vancouver Island, 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDCFFB23EF0FF39FA4853B8" box="[1272,1462,229,253]" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">British Columbia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB45DFFDCFFB23BE3FED4FAF85289" blockId="3.[491,1495,229,461]" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">
The fifth species from western North America, 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDCFFB239E2FED5FB765265" box="[1002,1160,264,288]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offarostrata">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDCFFB239E2FED5FB765265" box="[1002,1160,264,288]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">C. offarostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, named for a large ‘hump’ on the rostrum, is known only from a few locations on Vancouver Island and Haida Gwaii, 
<collectingRegion id="49E77ABFFFDCFFB23F7FFEF7FDA75220" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">British Columbia</collectingRegion>
. Morphological variation in 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDCFFB23985FE92FBD55220" box="[909,1067,333,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offarostrata">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDCFFB23985FE92FBD55220" box="[909,1067,333,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">C. offarostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Haida Gwaii needs to be compared with that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDCFFB23878FEACFD0452CD" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[624,762,368,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaerica">
C. 
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDCFFB23899FEACFD0452CD" box="[657,762,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">sphaerica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the distributional patterns of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDCFFB23E4BFEACFB3252CD" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[1091,1228,368,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaerica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDCFFB23E4BFEACFB3252CD" box="[1091,1228,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">C. sphaerica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggest this species is limited to arctic and subarctic areas in western 
<collectingCountry id="F334F4CDFFDCFFB239D5FE4EFBCF52EF" box="[989,1073,402,426]" name="Canada" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">Canada</collectingCountry>
, however, 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDCFFB23EAAFE4FFAC052EF" box="[1186,1342,402,426]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offarostrata">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDCFFB23EAAFE4FFAC052EF" box="[1186,1342,402,426]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">C. offarostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares several character states, and may be a southern variant subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23CFDEFFDCFFB23E7FFE69FB015288" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[1143,1279,437,461]" class="Arachnida" family="Ceratoppiidae" genus="Ceratoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaerica">
<emphasis id="B957684FFFDCFFB23E7FFE69FB015288" box="[1143,1279,437,461]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">C. sphaerica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
